223-233 West 67th Street, north side, between Amsterdam and West End Avenues. St. Matthews Hall at 223 West 67th Street, is in the center of the picture. This Hall is connected with St. Matthews Church, (Roman Catholic), at 215-217 West 67th Street.

September 14, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

title: Tenements & storefronts; Darrison's 5+10, A. Buchsbaum Butcher: 165-169 Amsterdam Av-W 67-W 68 St, Manhattan

text:
(1)
Amsterdam Ave., west side, south from West 69th to 67th Streets and showing a Public Library and a Public School (No. 94). The first is on the right and is No. 190-92 Amsterdam Ave., adjoining the structure at the S.W. corner of 69th Street. The Public School is at the N.W. corner of 68th Street.

December 19, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A portion of the preceding view, showing only the 68th to 69th Street block front, as viewed from Broadway, and across a gas station on the south side of 69th Street.

December 19, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
A detail, showing only the Riverside Branch of the New York Public Library.

December 19, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
